The Canadian women’s volleyball team finished fourth at the NORCECA continental championship in Mexico. 
Tabi Love of Dauphin posted 13 kills and a block as the Canadians dropped the third-place match 3-1 (23-25, 25-19, 25-20, 25-17) to Puerto Rico on Friday. Lucille Charuk added six kills and two blocks for Canada, while Aurea Cruz and Karina Ocasio both had 13 kills for Puerto Rico. Please subscribe to view full article.
